This article is a presidential memorandum from November 30, 2009. It assigns certain functions and responsibilities to various government departments and officials under the National Defense Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 2010, the Department of Homeland Security Appropriations Act, 2010, and the Department of the Interior, Environment, and Related Agencies Appropriations Act, 2010. The memorandum outlines the specific functions assigned to the Secretary of Defense, the Attorney General, and the Secretary of State regarding detainees and reporting requirements. The memorandum also states that any future statutory provisions that are the same or substantially similar to the referenced provisions shall be included. The Attorney General is authorized and directed to publish this memorandum in the Federal Register.